stories.text: Background: We are switching prod servers soon. Our dns provider only allows TTLs to go as low as 3600. I found dns.google/search which is helpful. Is there anything else like this for let's say cloud flare etc. ?
stories.title: Ask HN: Any sites like dns.google/cache?

stories.text: I wanted to know what the division assignment operator does in JavaScript. In my typical way of googling, I went to the url bar and typed /= in javascript. That yielded an error "Your file couldn’t be accessed." First time encountering something like that.
